<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Spin_(physics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://physics.nist.gov/cgi-bin/cuu/Value?gem" class="external text" title="http://physics.nist.gov/cgi-bin/cuu/Value?gem" rel="nofollow">"CODATA Value: electron g factor"</a>. <i>The NIST Reference on Constants, Units, and Uncertainty</i>. <a href="/wiki/National_Institute_of_Standards_and_Technology" title="National Institute of Standards and Technology">NIST</a>. 2006<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://physics.nist.gov/cgi-bin/cuu/Value?gem" class="external free" title="http://physics.nist.gov/cgi-bin/cuu/Value?gem" rel="nofollow">http://physics.nist.gov/cgi-bin/cuu/Value?gem</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-10-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=CODATA+Value%3A+electron+g+factor&amp;rft.atitle=The+NIST+Reference+on+Constants%2C+Units%2C+and+Uncertainty&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BNational+Institute+of+Standards+and+Technology%7CNIST%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fphysics.nist.gov%2Fcgi-bin%2Fcuu%2FValue%3Fgem&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Spin_(physics)"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BRichard_Feynman.7CR.P._Feynman.5D.5D1985"><a href="/wiki/Richard_Feynman" title="Richard Feynman">R.P. Feynman</a> (1985). "Electrons and Their Interactions". <i><a href="/wiki/QED:_The_Strange_Theory_of_Light_and_Matter" title="QED: The Strange Theory of Light and Matter">QED: The Strange Theory of Light and Matter</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Princeton,_New_Jersey" title="Princeton, New Jersey">Princeton, New Jersey</a>: <a href="/wiki/Princeton_University_Press" title="Princeton University Press">Princeton University Press</a>. p.&#160;115. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0691083886" class="internal">ISBN 0-691-08388-6</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Electrons+and+Their+Interactions&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BQED%3A+The+Strange+Theory+of+Light+and+Matter%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BRichard+Feynman%7CR.P.+Feynman%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BRichard+Feynman%7CR.P.+Feynman%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B115&amp;rft.place=%5B%5BPrinceton%2C+New+Jersey%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPrinceton+University+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-691-08388-6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Spin_(physics)"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span><br />
<dl>
<dd>"After some years, it was discovered that this value [−<i>g</i>/2] was not exactly 1, but slightly more—something like 1.00116. This correction was worked out for the first time in 1948 by Schwinger as <i>j</i>*<i>j</i> divided by 2 pi  [<i><a href="/wiki/Sic" title="Sic">sic</a></i>] [where <i>j</i> is the square root of the <a href="/wiki/Fine-structure_constant" title="Fine-structure constant">fine-structure constant</a>], and was due to an alternative way the electron can go from place to place: instead of going directly from one point to another, the electron goes along for a while and suddenly emits a photon; then (horrors!) it absorbs its own photon."</dd>
</dl>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFW.J._Marciano.2C_A.I._Sanda1977">W.J. Marciano, A.I. Sanda (1977). "Exotic decays of the muon and heavy leptons in gauge theories". <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Physics_Letters&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Physics Letters (page does not exist)">Physics Letters</a></i> <b>B67</b> (3): 303–305. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2F0370-2693%2877%2990377-X" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2F0370-2693%2877%2990377-X" rel="nofollow">10.1016/0370-2693(77)90377-X</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Exotic+decays+of+the+muon+and+heavy+leptons+in+gauge+theories&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BPhysics+Letters%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=W.J.+Marciano%2C+A.I.+Sanda&amp;rft.au=W.J.+Marciano%2C+A.I.+Sanda&amp;rft.date=1977&amp;rft.volume=B67&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=303%E2%80%93305&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1016%2F0370-2693%2877%2990377-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Spin_(physics)"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFB.W._Lee.2C_R.E._Shrock1977">B.W. Lee, R.E. Shrock (1977). "Natural suppression of symmetry violation in gauge theories: Muon- and electron-lepton-number nonconservation". <i><a href="/wiki/Physical_Review" title="Physical Review">Physical Review</a></i> <b>D16</b> (5): 1444–1473. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.16.1444" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.16.1444" rel="nofollow">10.1103/PhysRevD.16.1444</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Natural+suppression+of+symmetry+violation+in+gauge+theories%3A+Muon-+and+electron-lepton-number+nonconservation&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BPhysical+Review%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=B.W.+Lee%2C+R.E.+Shrock&amp;rft.au=B.W.+Lee%2C+R.E.+Shrock&amp;rft.date=1977&amp;rft.volume=D16&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=1444%E2%80%931473&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1103%2FPhysRevD.16.1444&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Spin_(physics)"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
